<br>
That says to me that you weren't really doing a whole lot to get a spot to try him, or at least not doing everything you could have been.  Endorean, Triad have both been rather generous to other guilds wanting to try VS, and Heroes has been willing, although not approached by any that I know of except for Sacred Sanctuary.... whom we offered to give up our turn to.<br>
<br>
Flarestar Bladesinger <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/upojokhickeneater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pojo Khickeneater</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Desert Madman</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/25/01 11:29:16 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ok WE KILLED v.s. now we want in</span><hr size=1> &quot;The system with VS has become a way to keep new guilds out. Before the Kunark dragons were heavily camped (i.e. when you could run from DL portal to KC everyday and always see Gore on track)... it was a different story, and the rotation was a good idea.&quot;<br>
<br>
Not true.  The way to get in was to kill a Kunark dragon in house to become part of the rotation.  Every guild that was in the rotation prior to this had done the same thing.  They asked a guild in the rotation for chance and took the mob out.  There is nothing exclusionary about it, and yes, it does take time, effort, and patience to get in.<br>
<br>
Yes, killing a Kunark dragon is not that easy because of the drops/epic pieces they can give along with being FFA.  It requires all of the things that have been talked about:  fast mobilization and being able to have the people online to get the job done.  Well, guess what, it's likely going to be the same way with VS now.  If you had difficulty in getting a Kunark dragon prior to this point with them being FFA, how well do you think you will fare if VS is indeed now FFA?<br>
<br>
&quot;Time to revamp the old system. Not go to FFA, but find a way to allow guilds into the rotation that is fair.&quot;<br>
<br>
Not going to argue that neccessarily since the rotation and calendar are not perfect, but why should any non rotation guild wanting to kill VS now do that since the precedent has been set that it is OK to treat the spawn as FFA?  Suggesting it now is kinda like closing the barn door after the horses have already run out.<br>
<br>
Laters.<br>
-Pojo <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uasetwyzerman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aset Wyzerman</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://wwp.icq.com/scripts/online.dll?icq=29870620&img=5 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Drolvarg Gnasher</span><br>  Posts: 701<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/25/01 2:57:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/fluclin71335dragonsandtheplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=888.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.luclin.org/files/aset/ISIS.gif width=90 height=45></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ok WE KILLED v.s. now we want in</span><hr size=1> Ok guys tell you what until you get a response like this after asking to be allowed in the rotation don't whine to me about working hard for it for 2 months.<br>
